verbs.description: immunize (third-person singular simple present immunizes, present participle immunizing, simple past and past participle immunized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make someone or something immune to something.
examples: It is now clear that the brevity of an indecent broadcast – be it word or image – cannot immunize it from FCC censure.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To inoculate someone, and thus produce immunity from a disease.
